Marqos mentioned as patriarch of Alexandria and  Mikaʾel as metropolitan of Ethiopia (fol. 113ra). Fasilädäs is mentioned as the king (fol. 13rb). 
Mark VI was the patriarch of Alexandria in 1645-60; 
Mikaʾel IV was the metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1650-63; King Fasilädäs reigned in 1632-67.
